text: Lake Rebecca is a lake in Hennepin County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. The lake has an area of with a max depth of and is found at the elevation of . Lake Rebecca was named for Rebecca Allen, the wife of Samuel Allen. ==See also== *List of lakes in Minnesota ==References== Category:Lakes of Minnesota Category:Lakes of Hennepin County, Minnesota
